    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are positioned for high-upside production today, headlined by **Gunnar Henderson** (83.29) and **Andy Pages** (75.64). **Gunnar Henderson** remains our primary catalyst; despite a slight negative adjustment for the stolen base challenge posed by the opposing battery, his lead-off role against a middling starter provides the highest efficiency ceiling on the roster. Meanwhile, **Andy Pages** benefits from the most favorable park factor of the day (+14%) and a high-leverage matchup against Quintana, making him a must-start for potential power-heavy returns. Both **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (74.56) and **Drake Baldwin** (72.11) also clear the 70-point threshold, capitalizing on soft matchups against Elder and Irvin, respectively.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today involved **Nolan Schanuel** (50.08), who fell just outside our \"Strong\" tier. While **Nolan Schanuel** projects for a respectable floor, he ultimately lost out to the superior platoon and park adjustments afforded to the rest of the infield, specifically **Brady House** and **Jacob Wilson**. We are exercising caution with **Josh Lowe** (53.92) and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (57.76), as both face difficult arms in Cease and Detmers, respectively; their scores reflect a significant SP skill penalty that suppresses their otherwise elite raw talent. We continue to monitor the status of **Kyle Tucker**, **Luis Robert Jr.**, and **Jackson Merrill**, who remain sidelined or inactive today, depriving the lineup of critical stolen base anchors. Owners should monitor weather reports, though no major atmospheric risks are currently flagging the slate, leaving our current configuration as the optimal path for maximizing R, HR, and RBI efficiency.",
